==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[subtractus]]'', p.p. of ''[[subtrahere]]'' to [[draw]] from [[beneath]], [[withdraw]], [[remove]]; ''[[sub]]'' under + ''[[trahere]]'' to draw

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-subtract.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Transitive verb===
{{wikipedia}}
'''subtract'''
#to [[remove]] or [[reduce]]; especially to reduce a [[quantity]] or [[number]]
#:''If you '''subtract''' the $100 for gas and bridge toll, it was a fairly inexpensive trip.''

